</taxonomicName>
by KG Blair (
<collectionCode box="[649,762,1654,1680]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34665" name="Natural History Museum, London" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="Museum">NHMUK</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1442,1695,1927]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,575,1695,1721]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Summary of diagnostic features.</emphasis>
Dorsal colour pale brown; 
<quantity box="[886,987,1695,1722]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.58" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="15.8">15.8 mm</quantity>
long; light organs in ventrite 7 bipartite and widely separated; median posterior area of ventrite 7 terminated by a single elongate slender apically acute ‘appendage’ which is considered to conform to 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier E." box="[717,888,1764,1791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="97 - 200" refId="ref6019" refString="Olivier E. 1886. Colophotia miranda. p. 186 - 187. In: Baer G-A. Catalogue des Coleopteres des Iles Philippines. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France 1886: 97 - 200." type="journal article" year="1886">Olivier’s (1886)</bibRefCitation>
description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1442,1695,1927]" box="[256,1180,1798,1825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
Male. 
<quantity box="[324,424,1798,1825]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.58" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="15.8">15.8 mm</quantity>
long; 
<quantity box="[492,577,1798,1824]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="6.8">6.8 mm</quantity>
wide measured at region of pin through right elytron.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1442,1695,1927]" lastBlockId="5.[191,1442,214,1819]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
Colour (
<figureCitation box="[353,473,1832,1858]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1A, B</figureCitation>
): Dorsal surface very pale brown; pronotum semitransparent with fat body showing irregularly through cuticle; head between eyes light brown, semitransparent, with fat body visible; left antenna with pale brown scape and remaining segments darker brown; right antenna colour ventral surface scape pale brown, pedicel and apical two segments dark brown, dorsal surface as for left; ventral surface of thorax and legs pale brown; abdomen in original state before immersion in any fluids with dorsum pale brown semitransparent and fat bodies visible beneath cuticle in all but terminal tergite; ventral surface with 
<collectionCode box="[1168,1189,281,307]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
2−4 pale brown semitransparent, 
<collectionCode box="[337,358,314,341]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
5 slightly paler, 
<collectionCode box="[540,560,314,340]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
6 with 
<collectionCode box="[641,677,315,341]" country="Sweden" name="Type Collection" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">LO</collectionCode>
plaques adhering to lateral areas of ventrite appearing mid brown and intervening area semitransparent with irregular distribution of fat body beneath; anterior area of 
<collectionCode box="[1334,1354,349,375]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
<quantity box="[1354,1396,348,375]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
dry specimen with lateral brown 
<collectionCode box="[524,560,382,408]" country="Sweden" name="Type Collection" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">LO</collectionCode>
plaques and an apparent posterior margin separating this from the posterior area which is encircled by paler brown 
<collectionCode box="[647,694,416,442]" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15781" name="Institute of Himalayan Bioresource Technology" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Herbarium">PLP</collectionCode>
incurving, and was covered in light brown material of unknown origin; after soaking in KOH all of the ventral surface of the 
<collectionCode box="[890,947,449,475]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MPP</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1005,1051,449,475]" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15781" name="Institute of Himalayan Bioresource Technology" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Herbarium">PLP</collectionCode>
, and a narrow area anterior to the emarginations appears to be clumped fat body beneath. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[977,1099,482,509]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1A, B</figureCitation>
): 3.0 mm long, 
<quantity box="[1284,1372,483,509]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
wide; anterior margin broadly rounded scarcely projecting beyond the rounded obtuse anterolateral corners; lateral margins diverging in anterior half and pronotum widest across middle; lateral margins converge posteriorly with slightly angulate posterior corners not behind anterior corners but to the sides; posterior corners slightly obtuse; median posterior margin shallowly emarginated and projecting a little beyond the posterior corners; most of dorsal surface smooth with flattened and widely explanate lateral margins; median area of disc a little elevated and shallow depressions just behind anterior margin behind head, and across and in front of posterior margin, not extending to laterally explanate region; pronotal width slightly less than humeral width. Elytra (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
): 
<quantity box="[250,352,751,778]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.28" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="12.8">12.8 mm</quantity>
long; no elevated interstitial lines; lateral margins slightly convex sided; with wide epipleuron extending laterally just behind anterior margin of hypomeron and diminishing in width towards elytral apex. Head (
<figureCitation box="[271,360,818,845]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
): GHW 
<quantity box="[461,552,819,845]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
; SIW 
<quantity box="[625,715,819,845]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
; 
<collectionCode box="[729,782,819,845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">ASD</collectionCode>
subequal to 
<collectionCode box="[934,995,819,845]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/fx5p-e4j3" name="Culture Collection of Algae at the University of Vienna" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">ASW</collectionCode>
; vertex barely depressed between eyes. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[316,401,852,878]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
): 11 segmented, three times as long as GHW, with elongate scape, small pedicel and all flagellar segments longer than wide; FS 1–7 four times as long as wide; FS 8 ¾ as long as FS 7, and FS 9 ¾ as long as FS8. Mouthparts (
<figureCitation box="[398,485,919,945]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
): well developed and male can probably feed; apical labial palpomere in the form of an elongate slender triangle (L 4–5 × W) with inner margin entire. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1104,953,979]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
): no tibiae swollen or curved; hind femora stout slightly wider than femora 1 and 2. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[918,1002,986,1013]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1014,1030,987,1013]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,272,1234,1260]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-200@7.[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Abdomen of Colophotia miranda male. A) V6 and V7, dorsal; B) V6 and V7 ventral with single apical appendage (C), muscle attachments (i, ii, iii) indicated; C) posterior view ventrites uppermost, single apical appendage indicated; D–F) Tergite 8. D – dorsal, E – right lateral (flanges indicated, muscles blocks arrowed), F – ventral (muscles blocks arrowed). Figure legends: LO – light organ; MPP – median posterior projection; PLP – posterolateral projection; T8 – tergite 8; V6 – ventrite 6; V7 – ventrite 7; i, ii, iii – muscle attachments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041743/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">2</figureCitation>
): 
<collectionCode box="[1049,1071,986,1012]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
6: appears to have no light organs in the median area and they may be emarginated in this segment, or the median area devoid of light organ is a consequence of some aspect of dehydration and the dissection, as there are no obvious muscle attachments in the median area of 
<collectionCode box="[412,434,1087,1113]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
6; 
<collectionCode box="[459,481,1088,1114]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
7: with broadly and evenly emarginated anterior margin (not obvious in intact specimen); lateral margins converging posteriorly; posterior margin trisinuate (
<figureCitation box="[1036,1152,1121,1147]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,272,1234,1260]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-200@7.[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Abdomen of Colophotia miranda male. A) V6 and V7, dorsal; B) V6 and V7 ventral with single apical appendage (C), muscle attachments (i, ii, iii) indicated; C) posterior view ventrites uppermost, single apical appendage indicated; D–F) Tergite 8. D – dorsal, E – right lateral (flanges indicated, muscles blocks arrowed), F – ventral (muscles blocks arrowed). Figure legends: LO – light organ; MPP – median posterior projection; PLP – posterolateral projection; T8 – tergite 8; V6 – ventrite 6; V7 – ventrite 7; i, ii, iii – muscle attachments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041743/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
) with oblique 
<collectionCode box="[1317,1364,1121,1147]" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15781" name="Institute of Himalayan Bioresource Technology" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Herbarium">PLP</collectionCode>
which are half the length of the 
<collectionCode box="[476,533,1155,1181]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MPP</collectionCode>
and curve inwards partly embracing the 
<collectionCode box="[997,1054,1155,1181]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MPP</collectionCode>
in dried specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1365,1154,1181]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[192,272,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[274,1354,213,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-89@6.[192,1440,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Colophotia miranda male. A) Habitus dorsal and ventral with epipleuron arrowed; B) Detail head and pronotum, with arrows at margins of the median elevated area of disc; C) Specimen label; D) Dried specimen before dissection, abdominal ventrites showing actual number of ventrite, with T8, LO situated on V6 and V7. Figure legends: LO – light organ; T8 – tergite 8; V2 – ventrite 2; V5 – ventrite 5; V7 – ventrite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041741/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
); deep slightly irregular emarginations separate 
<collectionCode box="[654,711,1189,1215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MPP</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[767,816,1189,1215]" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15781" name="Institute of Himalayan Bioresource Technology" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Herbarium">PLP</collectionCode>
; 
<collectionCode box="[826,883,1189,1215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MPP</collectionCode>
broad and deep with concave dorsal surface; apically truncated with a single elongate very slender apically acute appendage arising from the left side of the apex, and remaining margins densely hairy; dorsal surface 
<collectionCode box="[797,817,1256,1282]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
7 with brown facing cuticle covering sides of 
<collectionCode box="[1332,1389,1256,1282]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MPP</collectionCode>
and around emarginations to the 
<collectionCode box="[522,568,1289,1315]" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15781" name="Institute of Himalayan Bioresource Technology" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Herbarium">PLP</collectionCode>
. Muscle attachments (
<figureCitation box="[817,934,1289,1315]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,272,1234,1260]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-200@7.[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Abdomen of Colophotia miranda male. A) V6 and V7, dorsal; B) V6 and V7 ventral with single apical appendage (C), muscle attachments (i, ii, iii) indicated; C) posterior view ventrites uppermost, single apical appendage indicated; D–F) Tergite 8. D – dorsal, E – right lateral (flanges indicated, muscles blocks arrowed), F – ventral (muscles blocks arrowed). Figure legends: LO – light organ; MPP – median posterior projection; PLP – posterolateral projection; T8 – tergite 8; V6 – ventrite 6; V7 – ventrite 7; i, ii, iii – muscle attachments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041743/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
): a large block of longitudinal muscles attach on the median area of 
<collectionCode box="[441,461,1323,1349]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
7 between light organ halves and narrow to a median band along the dorsal median surface of the 
<collectionCode box="[312,371,1357,1383]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MPP</collectionCode>
; in the anterior portion these muscles split into two wide bands attaching to the anterior margin on either side of the anterior emargination of 
<collectionCode box="[698,720,1390,1416]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
7; small lateral bands reach the sides anterior to the 
<collectionCode box="[1292,1341,1390,1416]" country="India" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15781" name="Institute of Himalayan Bioresource Technology" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="Herbarium">PLP</collectionCode>
; 
<collectionCode box="[1350,1368,1390,1416]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">T</collectionCode>
8 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,272,1234,1260]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-200@7.[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Abdomen of Colophotia miranda male. A) V6 and V7, dorsal; B) V6 and V7 ventral with single apical appendage (C), muscle attachments (i, ii, iii) indicated; C) posterior view ventrites uppermost, single apical appendage indicated; D–F) Tergite 8. D – dorsal, E – right lateral (flanges indicated, muscles blocks arrowed), F – ventral (muscles blocks arrowed). Figure legends: LO – light organ; MPP – median posterior projection; PLP – posterolateral projection; T8 – tergite 8; V6 – ventrite 6; V7 – ventrite 7; i, ii, iii – muscle attachments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041743/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2 D–F</figureCitation>
): lateral margins straight converging slightly posteriorly; median posterior margin with a deep and narrow emargination, margined by acute corners, and further shallow lateral emarginations between median area and rounded posterolateral corners; dorsal surface with deep median longitudinal emargination which houses the aedeagus and sheath in repose and distinct acute margins separating this median channel from flat side areas which have no spines; there is no muscle attachment posterior to the flanges in 
<collectionCode box="[1072,1091,1558,1584]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">T</collectionCode>
8; strongly sclerotized and dark flanges with obliquely truncated apices each projecting posteriorly arise at the anterior end of the acute margins of the median trough; anterolateral paired prolongations of 
<collectionCode box="[877,895,1625,1651]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">T</collectionCode>
8 rounded and slightly shorter than the median length of the entire posterior portion. Muscle attachments (
<figureCitation box="[880,1001,1658,1685]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,272,1234,1260]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-200@7.[192,1440,213,1204]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Abdomen of Colophotia miranda male. A) V6 and V7, dorsal; B) V6 and V7 ventral with single apical appendage (C), muscle attachments (i, ii, iii) indicated; C) posterior view ventrites uppermost, single apical appendage indicated; D–F) Tergite 8. D – dorsal, E – right lateral (flanges indicated, muscles blocks arrowed), F – ventral (muscles blocks arrowed). Figure legends: LO – light organ; MPP – median posterior projection; PLP – posterolateral projection; T8 – tergite 8; V6 – ventrite 6; V7 – ventrite 7; i, ii, iii – muscle attachments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041743/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2 E, F</figureCitation>
): strong bands of longitudinal muscles attach onto the basal portion of the flanges. Aedeagal sheath 
<figureCitation box="[882,1008,1692,1718]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[429,509,1364,1390]" captionTargetBox="[429,1202,213,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-233@8.[429,1202,213,1332]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Genitalia of Colophotia miranda male. A–C) Aedeagal" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041745/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 3 A–C</figureCitation>
): elongate slender about 7 × as long as wide; tergite of sheath in two sections; anterior margin evenly emarginated. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1326,1726,1752]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[429,509,1364,1390]" captionTargetBox="[429,1202,213,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-233@8.[429,1202,213,1332]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Genitalia of Colophotia miranda male. A–C) Aedeagal" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5041745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5041745/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 3 D–F</figureCitation>
): elongate slender about 6 × as long as wide; appearing slightly asymmetrical (basal piece is turned to one side); lateral lobes very short scarcely separated.
